cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to classify Yelp reviews as positive/negative and 5-star rating. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract features from the text, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning models such as Naive Bayes, Support Vector Machines, and Logistic Regression makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to classify the reviews, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of online reviews, which can be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
